make sense. Our viewpoint isn't a single point in the center of our skull,
after all. I want to talk to my buddy Mike at Valve about this and get back
to you. He holds a PhD in Visual Cognition and he worked a lot with the VR
team on various improvements. It would surprise me greatly if this wasn't
something that he'd already done some work on.

Obviously, on the VR project, immersion and realism were top priorities.
But above those was "players shouldn't get sick" so any novel ideas that
produced an improved result for some of the audience but created problems
for others would likely have been scrapped.

Either way, Mike will produce some more interesting insight than I would.

